@startuml ddc_recovery_state
' Created 2026-05-13: per claudeit/_diagram_amendments.md
!include dark-theme.puml
title DDC recovery state machine\nEvent-triggered fallback worker re-enters acquisition

' Per-monitor recovery state lives on MonitorInfo (SliderState + IsReadDegraded)
state Healthy : SliderState != Failed\n!IsReadDegraded
state Failed : SliderState == Failed\nLastDDCError set\n_entries.Remove, _writeThrottler.Drop
state ReadDegraded : SliderState != Failed\nIsReadDegraded == true\nSlider operable, reads fail

[*] --> Healthy

Healthy --> Failed : DoBrightnessWriteAsync exhausted (:1769-1784)\nOR VerifyAppliedAsync exhausted (:1822-1882)\nOR Refresh re-probe failure (:603-612)\nOR WasEverDDCCapable monitor disappeared (:475-491)

Failed --> Healthy : fallback Refresh acquisition succeeds\n(PromoteRecovered / Refresh promotion)
Failed --> Failed : fallback Refresh acquisition still fails

ReadDegraded --> Healthy : fallback Refresh read succeeds\n(IsReadDegraded=false)
ReadDegraded --> Failed : writes start failing\n(BeginInvoke at :1295-1312)

note bottom of Failed
  MonitorsRefreshed sets one global DDC recovery-needed flag
  when GetStuckRecoveryCandidateIds returns any Failed or
  ReadDegraded known-DDC rows.

  DDCRecoveryService starts one worker, waits 2 seconds, then
  calls MonitorService.Refresh. That reuses the same read-only
  acquisition path as startup/topology. No per-monitor workers,
  no terminal abandonment, and no brightness writes inside acquisition.
end note

note bottom of ReadDegraded
  ReadDegraded monitors STAY candidates.
  A successful fallback Refresh read clears IsReadDegraded.
  A write failure demotes to Failed so the same fallback worker
  keeps trying acquisition.
end note

' Primitives explicitly NOT present (verified absent at commit 4b5600b)
note as N_ABSENT
  Primitives the project does NOT have today:
  - CCD soft-replug (SetDisplayConfig deactivate/reactivate). CCD.cs has
    only the read-only trio.
  - PnPCycle (SetupDi disable/enable). No PnPDeviceService.cs.
  - ElevationService / AllowPnPRecovery setting / install-elevation-task.
  - VCP 0x04 factory reset (user-excluded per feedback memory).
  Hard power-off VCP 0xD6 is user-initiated only (Ctrl+click).
end note

@enduml
